Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Cream together butter or margarine and butter. Add sugar , flour, baking powder, 1 egg , vanilla, ground cinnamon, nutmeg and milk. Chill dough until easy to handle. On a floured board roll tablespoon size pieces into ropes. Place on cookie sheet in S shapes. Brush with remaining egg that is beaten with 1 tablespoon water. Sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degree C) for 10 to 12 minutes.